A sudden fire that erupted this afternoon at Six Flags Magic Mountain has collapsed one of the park's famed roller coasters, tearing away a section of track.

Los Angeles County firefighters were called to the park in Santa Clarita, California at around 1:30 pm Monday after the wooden coaster Colossus became engulfed in flames.

Luckily, the coaster had been shut down since last month and no injuries have been reported, according to KTLA.

