New coaster: The fire was caused by welders working on the coaster, which is being updated into the new ride Twisted Colossus (above)

The ride is currently in the process of being taken down and replaced with a new, updated coaster, Twisted Colossus.

The amusement park announced less than two weeks ago it would turn the roller coaster into a wood and steel hybrid, with inverted loops added to the existing wooden structure.

The plans for the overhaul include removing over 3,000 feet of track to accommodate the new sections.

Fire inspector Miller told the Los Angeles Times that further collapse of the coaster did not appear likely.

 

